  /* --- catalog-forks-breadth-3 (2026-07-09): X-Fusion breadth. The prior session's lone Trace36 row (corrected above) had NO source at all - it turns out the previous x-fusionshox.com lookup DNS-failed on a stray hyphen; the real domain xfusionshox.com fetches cleanly, including individual product-detail pages with real spec tables ("products_detail/<id>.htm" - ids discovered by asking the fetch tool to read hrefs off each category listing page, e.g. products/21_31.htm for RC32). Five more real X-Fusion fork families added below: RC32 (XC, 27.5/29, 32mm), Sweep Boost (trail/AM, 27.5, 34mm), Slide Boost (trail/AM/E-MTB, 29, 34mm), Vengeance 38 (enduro, 29, 38mm), RV1 38 DH (DH dual-crown, 27.5/29, 38mm). Each model ships in 2-3 damper trims (HLR/RCP/RC) that share one chassis/interfaces - per this catalog's established convention of cataloging one flagship trim per chassis (RockShox=Ultimate only, Fox=Factory only), only the HLR trim (X-Fusion's top damper) is entered per travel/wheel point; RC32/Vengeance/RV1 have no separate damper-trim naming so are entered as-is. Every wheel/travel/axle/steerer/rotor field below traces to a FETCHED xfusionshox.com product-detail page; travel points are the ones explicitly given in each page's own "ITA" (Internal Travel Adjust) list, never an interpolated value. A non-Boost, QR "9mm x 100mm"-axle base RC32 variant also exists on the site (products_detail lookup found it as "RC32 XC (27.5)") but is skipped - that axle spacing has no vocab value in this catalog and isn't worth widening schema.js for a legacy entry-level QR fork. --- */
