  /* =========================================================================
     COMPLETE BIKES — Pivot + Yeti cluster (2026-07-15). Pivot's own site
     (pivotcycles.com / global.pivotcycles.com) is a documented fetch blocker:
     the marketing shell renders (confirmed via the Browser pane) but the
     "Build Specs"/price tab never populates any text in either WebFetch or a
     rendered headless pass, and jensonusa.com/99spokes.com direct product
     pages 403 WebFetch (Cloudflare bot-walled). Every Pivot build below is
     therefore sourced from a FETCHED vitalmtb.com product-guide page (a
     third-party spec database that reprints the maker's own build sheet) or a
     FETCHED 99spokes.com page (rendered via the Browser pane, which is NOT
     bot-walled the way its Cloudflare-fronted WebFetch route is) - both are
     third-party per DATA-ENTRY-TEMPLATE.md rule 5, so every Pivot completebike
     row here stays SAMPLE (no verified:true, no source field on the row).
     Yeti's site (yeticycles.com) DOES fetch cleanly and DOES publish real
     build-kit prices directly (confirmed this session: yeticycles.com/en-us/
     bikes/<model> renders a "Manufacturer Price" list with a headline
     fork/shock/drivetrain/brake summary per build) - but it does NOT publish
     the granular wheel/tire/cockpit/dropper/saddle spec needed to fill every
     slot without guessing, so the full per-slot build sheet for each Yeti row
     below is filled from a FETCHED 99spokes.com page for the SAME model+year+
     trim (cross-checked against the Yeti-fetched price/fork/shock/drivetrain
     headline where the trims line up). Because the full fills list is only
     confirmed via the third-party 99spokes page, these rows also stay SAMPLE
     per rule 5 (the Yeti-fetched headline alone does not cover every slot).
     A real, load-bearing generation trap was caught while sourcing these:
     Yeti's own support article ("What cranks and bottom bracket can I use on
     the ARC?") states the ARC ships PF92 press-fit - but the ALREADY-VERIFIED
     fr-yeti-arc frame row in this catalog (sourced 2026-07-10 from the MY25
     owner manual) carries bb:'BSA73'. This looks like a genuine data error in
     that existing verified row (flagged for the coordinator/next audit - NOT
     corrected here, out of this cluster's scope and a verified row shouldn't
     be touched without re-confirming the manual PDF firsthand); the ARC
     completebike row below deliberately OMITS the bb slot fill so no build
     depends on which of the two conflicting facts is right. Similarly, the
     2024-model-year Pivot Switchblade builds on 99spokes are a DIFFERENT,
     newer "V3" generation (142mm rear travel becomes a different geometry/
     shock size per its own reviews) from the already-cataloged
     fr-pivot-switchblade-v2 (2020-2023, travel:142/maxForkTravel:160) - the
     Switchblade row below deliberately uses a 2023-model-year 99spokes build
     (142/160mm suspension figures cross-checked to match the cataloged V2
     frame exactly) rather than a same-named-but-different-generation 2024+
     build, avoiding the classic id/generation collapse trap.
     ========================================================================= */

